  <prompt>
    Register a new `compose-editor` section type in the SpaarkeAi `SECTION_REGISTRY` so the Compose workspace layout can mount the TipTap editor shell as a workspace section. This is the foundational registry entry that allows the layout-driven shell to render the Compose surface. The actual `ComposeWorkspace.tsx` is built in Task 042; here we only wire the registry entry (id, displayName, factory pointer, default-config shape) following the precedent set by the Calendar workspace widget (Pattern D).
  </prompt>

  <role>
    Senior React/TypeScript developer with deep familiarity with the SpaarkeAi workspace layout system (`SECTION_REGISTRY`), Calendar workspace widget precedent (Pattern D), and Fluent UI v9 conventions.
  </role>

  <goal>
    `SECTION_REGISTRY` contains a `compose-editor` entry (matching the Phase 1 `sprk_workspacelayout.sprk_definitionjson` reference) that lazy-loads `ComposeWorkspace` once Task 042 lands. Build green; ui-test green; dark mode renders.
  </goal>

  <context>
    <background>
      FR-02 requires the `compose-editor` section type to be registered so the Compose layout (Phase 1, Task 010) can mount it. Pattern D (Calendar) is the canonical precedent — same lib, thin LW shim, dual-use registry entry. The registry entry is the smallest additive UI change that unblocks Tasks 042 + 045.
    </background>
  </context>

  <constraints>
    <constraint source="ADR-021">Section UI MUST use Fluent UI v9 semantic tokens; MUST honor dark mode via `useThemeContext`.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-028">Spaarke Auth v2 — section consumes client SSO context via `@spaarke/auth`; do NOT re-acquire tokens.</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">REUSE existing `SECTION_REGISTRY` extension pattern (Calendar precedent); NO new registry abstraction.</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">No custom DOCX-feature integration outside TipTap OOB — the registry entry only references the OOB-only Compose shell.</constraint>
  </constraints>

  <justification>
    <existing>`SECTION_REGISTRY` already exists in the SpaarkeAi shell (mounts Calendar, Conversation, Context, etc.). This task ADDS one entry. Verified via grep `SECTION_REGISTRY` in `src/solutions/SpaarkeAi/src/components/shell/`.</existing>
    <extension>Yes — extends an existing registry by one row; no new abstraction created. The section TYPE (`compose-editor`) is new, but the registry mechanism is unchanged.</extension>
    <cost-of-doing-nothing>FR-02 fails — the Compose layout (Phase 1) references an unregistered section type, so opening Compose renders nothing (silent layout mount failure). Tasks 042 + 045 cannot ship without this entry.</cost-of-doing-nothing>
  </justification>

